message.content:
cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the design and implementation of network slicing for industrial communication networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of network calculus to assess the end-to-end properties of the network slices. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the transformation of industrial production into Industry 4.0, which involves the integration of cyber-physical systems and control systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of network slicing as a mechanism to handle the diverse set of requirements to the network, which could involve the use of AI techniques. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the abstraction level for slicing deterministic and packet-switched industrial communication protocols, which involves software engineering principles.
